# Prescyent — Local Settings (example)

> Copy this file to `.claude/prescyent.local.md` in your project (or working folder) and fill in the values that apply. The `/discover` skill reads it at Phase 2a; if `Company Name` and `Your Role` are filled in, the skill skips the scope-confirmation questions and runs the audit directly.
>
> Empty fields fall back to defaults or get asked at runtime. Delete sections you don't want to set.

---

## Company

**Company name:** Acme Corp

---

## Caller

**Your role:** founder

> Pick one: `founder`, `cfo`, `ops`, `sales`, `marketing`, `product`, `other`

**Buyer intent:** ai-readiness

> Pick one:
> - `ai-readiness` — understand current AI readiness
> - `capture-senior-knowledge` — capture senior knowledge before someone leaves
> - `claude-actually-useful` — make Claude actually useful for the team
> - `other`

---

## Search

**Depth:** standard

> Pick one:
> - `standard` — top 10–15 sources, faster
> - `deep` — broader sweep, slower

**Max sources:** 15

---

## Known starting points (optional)

If there are specific docs, folders, or systems Prescyent should prioritize, list them. Bullet format. Skip the section entirely if you'd rather Prescyent cast a wide net.

- HubSpot deal pipeline (especially `Qualified` → `Closed Won` stages)
- Drive: `Sales Playbook 2026` folder
- Notion: `Operations` workspace, "How we run sales" page
- Fathom: last 30 days of customer calls

---

## Primary pain (optional)

What's been frustrating? One paragraph max. The audit subagents calibrate against this — they prioritize findings that match the pain you describe.

> Sales reps don't update HubSpot, leadership flies blind on pipeline. We've added reminders, automated tasks, and 1:1 reviews. Nothing sticks.

---

## Off-limits (optional)

Spaces or sources Prescyent should NOT read. Bullet format.

- Anything tagged `legal-restricted`
- HR transcripts from exit interviews
- `Board minutes` folder in Drive

---

## Notes for the next caller (optional)

Free text. Anything you want future runs of `/discover` to know about your setup, your team, your goals.

> We're a 40-person revops org. Two recent acquisitions still being integrated — Acme South (joined 2025) and Northwind (joined 2026). Their stacks haven't fully migrated; assume Salesforce data is fragmented.
